  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection and Psychological Support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this project is to protect displaced children from violence  abuse  exploitation and lack of care and promote their psychosocial wellbeing by building a protective environment around them. Outcome 1: A protective environment is built for children living in 9 displacement sites in targeted areas through the identification  strengthening and mobilisation of community-based child protection mechanisms. Outcome 2: The psychosocial wellbeing of 2700 children/youths living in nine displacement sites within targeted areas is promoted through psychosocial initiatives undertaken in the community and schools. Outcome 3: Child Protection outcomes are achieved throughout programming by mainstreaming and integrating child protection in the work of all programme sectors.</narrative>
  </description>
